# Layout & Container Max-Widths

Use these values for the main content wrapper so layout stays consistent across the app.

## Primary content containers

- **List/dashboard pages** (Cases, Communications, Contracts, Opportunities, Dashboard, Settings, Performance, Customer list pages, Cases summary):  
  `max-w-[1600px]` with `mx-auto` and `p-density-xl` (or `p-6` where density isn’t used).  
  Example: `<div className="mx-auto w-full min-w-0 max-w-[1600px] p-density-xl">`

- **Detail/content pages** (Case detail, Contact detail, Pipeline detail):  
  `max-w-[1400px]` with `mx-auto` and `w-full min-w-0` where needed.  
  Example: `<div className="mx-auto w-full min-w-0 max-w-[1400px]">`

## Narrower layouts

- **900px**: CRM home (`app/crm/page.tsx`), Customer landing, Customer account detail.
- **1000px**: Customer org detail.
- **720px**: Changelog, simple single-column pages.

## Modals and dialogs

- Prefer Tailwind presets: `max-w-lg`, `max-w-md`, `max-w-sm` for standard dialogs/sheets.
- Large modals (e.g. New Case): use explicit values like `max-w-[720px]` when needed.

## Conventions

- Do not introduce new arbitrary max-widths without matching one of the above categories.
- Prefer `min-w-0` on flex/grid children that contain the container to avoid overflow.
- If adding a global CSS variable for container width later (e.g. `--tally-container-max`), use it in Tailwind and reference it in this rule.
